Cleaned and Transformed dataset


matches <- read.csv("archive3/WorldCupMatches.csv")
players <- read.csv("archive3/WorldCupPlayers.csv")
world_cups <- read.csv("archive3/WorldCups.csv")
shoot_outs <- read.csv("archive2/shootouts.csv")

matches_clean <- matches %>%
    mutate(total_goals = (matches$Home.Team.Goals + matches$Away.Team.Goals))

matches_clean <- matches_clean %>%
    mutate(team_win = (ifelse(Home.Team.Goals > Away.Team.Goals, "Home",
        ifelse(Home.Team.Goals < Away.Team.Goals, "Away", "Draw")))) %>%
    drop_na()

home_df <- data.frame(Country = matches$Home.Team.Name, Goals = matches$Home.Team.Goals,
    Year = matches$Year)
away_df <- data.frame(Country = matches$Away.Team.Name, Goals = matches$Away.Team.Goals,
    Year = matches$Year)

home <- na.omit(home_df)
away <- na.omit(away_df)

country_goals <- rbind(home, away)

shoot_outs <- shoot_outs %>%
    mutate(winner = as_factor(winner))

players_split <- initial_split(players, prop = 0.75)
cups_split <- initial_split(world_cups, prop = 0.75)
fifa_split <- initial_split(matches_clean, prop = 0.75)

players_train <- training(players_split)
players_test <- testing(players_split)

cups_train <- training(cups_split)
cups_test <- testing(cups_split)

fifa_train <- training(fifa_split)
fifa_test <- testing(fifa_split)

Top 50 Countries in Total Goals Scored in World Cup


goals_country <- country_goals %>%
    select(-Year)
goals_country <- country_goals %>%
    mutate(Country = as.factor(Country))


goals_hist <- goals_country %>%
    ggplot() + aes(x = Goals, y = fct_lump_n(fct_rev(fct_infreq(Country)),
    n = 20), label = Goals) + geom_col() + labs(x = "Total Goals Scored in World Cup",
    y = "Country", title = "Top 20 Countries in World Cup Goals Scored",
    caption = "*disregard other") + theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 30),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 30, face = "bold"))
goals_hist



ggplot(goals_country, aes(fct_lump_n(fct_rev(fct_infreq(Country)), n = 20))) +
    geom_histogram(stat = "count", binwidth = 50) + coord_flip() + labs(x = "Country",
    y = "Total Games Played in World Cup", title = "Top 20 Countries in World Cup Games Played",
    caption = "*disregard other") + theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 30),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 30, face = "bold"))

Chart showing the amount of goals scored all-time per country in the world cup.

Home Field Advantage


matches_clean <- matches_clean %>%
    mutate(team_win = as.factor(team_win))
country_goals <- country_goals %>%
    mutate(country_simple = fct_lump(Country, n = 10))
matches_clean <- matches_clean %>%
    mutate(home_simple = fct_lump(Home.Team.Name, n = 10))
matches_clean <- matches_clean %>%
    mutate(away_simple = fct_lump(Away.Team.Name, n = 10))


home_chart <- ggplot(data = matches_clean, aes(x = "", y = team_win, fill = team_win)) +
    geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity")

home_pie <- home_chart + coord_polar("y", start = 0) + labs(title = "Match Outcome per Home or Away",
    y = "Outcome", x = "Team")
home_pie

Pie chart showing win share between home and away teams.

Top 50 Countries in Total Shootout Wins in World Cup


shoot_outs <- shoot_outs %>%
    mutate(winner_topten = fct_lump_n(winner, n = 10))

shoot_outs <- shoot_outs %>%
    mutate(winner_topten = fct_infreq(winner_topten))

winner_subset <- shoot_outs[shoot_outs$winner_topten %in% c("South Korea",
    "Zambia", "Egypt", "Argentina", "South Africa", "Thailand", "Kenya ",
    "Brazil", "Iraq", "Senegal"), ]
ggplot(winner_subset, aes(x = fct_rev(winner_topten))) + geom_histogram(stat = "count") +
    coord_flip() + labs(title = "Top 10 Shootout Winners", x = "Country",
    y = "Shootout wins")

Chart showing top 10 countries with the most shootout wins in World Cup history
